Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to turn on the Master Bedroom - Nightstands to 70% brightness.
2. The ramp rate should be fast, so choose a short ramp rate enum value (e.g., 0.1 seconds [31]).
3. The trigger condition is when the Patio Lights are turned off physically, which is a COC event with command "Fast Off" (DFOF) from Patio Lights.
4. The action is to set the Master Bedroom - Nightstands On Level to 70% and Ramp Rate to 0.1 seconds, then turn it on.
5. Use the Ramp Rate command first, then On Level, then On command to ensure proper ramping.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Master Bedroom Nightstands on Patio Lights Fast Off",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Patio Lights",
        "coc": "DFOF"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "Master Bedroom - Nightstands",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 31, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Master Bedroom - Nightstands",
        "command": "On Level",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "On Level", "value": 70, "uom": "%", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Master Bedroom - Nightstands",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Level", "value": 70, "uom": "%", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
